verbose_text: For carboxy fluoroscein succinimidyl ester (CFSE) labeling, splenocytes, MLN lymphocytes and lung lymphocytes from CFP exosomes +/-CpG adjuvant, and UT exosomes treated mice were labeled with CFSE (2.5 muM), and 1x10 6 cells / well were seeded in 24-well tissue culture plates in 500 muL of RPMI-1640 (supplemented with 10% heat inactivated FCS, 25 mM HEPES, 2 mM l-glutamine, 1 mM sodium pyruvate, 100 IU/mL penicillin and 100 mug/mL streptomycin) in the presence or absence of CFP (10 mug/mL).
evidence: heat-inactivated FCS, 25 mM HEPES, 2 mM l-glutamine
